Part A of the
			 Controlled Substances Act (21 U.S.C. 801 et seq.) is amended by adding at the
			 end the following:

the applicant (or if the applicant is a
				corporation, any of its officers, directors, or principal stockholders) has
				been convicted of a disqualifying offense;

prescribe the
				manner and form of applications for permits under this title (including the
				facts to be set forth in the application);
